videos.headline: Chahal to Bhuvneshwar, out Bowled!! That's a fourth for Yuzi!! Looks like that Purple Cap might never leave him... This was flat and turned the other way. Bhuvneshwar backed away for a big hit and played the wrong line, losing his stumps in the process. Bhuvneshwar b Chahal 6(10)

Chahal to Adil Rashid, out Stumped!! Adil Rashid uses his feet and Chahal bowls it wider and slower through the air. Adil Rashid swings at it ages early and misses. An easy stumping for Samson. Strangely, it has been taken usptairs to check for a stumping. The replay confirms that Adil Rashid was miles out. Adil Rashid st Samson b Chahal 18(13) [4s-1 6s-1]

Chahal to Mayank, out Caught by Buttler!! The procession conttinues for SRH! Wrong 'un on a full length outside off, Mayank gets low in his stance attempting to slog-sweep it. All he manages is to slice it off the toe-end of the bat towards long-off and Buttler is safe as houses. Mayank c Buttler b Chahal 27(23) [4s-3]

Ashwin to Glenn Phillips, out Caught by KM Asif!! SRH are in dire straits now! Ashwin joins the party as well and has a big smile on his face. Tossed up full ball outside off, luring Glenn Phillips to go for an audacious stroke. He obliges and goes for a full-fledged uppish drive but he makes the mistake of hitting it straight to extra cover. Also, he got it off the bottom half of the bat. KM Asif stationed there takes a sharp catch. Glenn Phillips c KM Asif b Ashwin 8(6) [6s-1]

Holder to Washington Sundar, out Caught by Hetmyer!! Another one bites the dust! The short ball proves to be the undoing for Sundar! Holder hits the deck hard and doesn't provide any room to the batter to play with. Although he is cramped for room, he goes for a pull across the line but ends up getting it off the toe-end of the bat. The ball lobs up towards mid-off. Hetmyer charges in from extra cover and takes it safely. Washington Sundar c Hetmyer b Holder 1(5)

Chahal to Harry Brook, out Bowled!! Chahal strikes and that ends a scratchy first innings for Harry Brook in the IPL! 300 wickets for Chahal in T20s, informs the on air commentator. He bowls it quicker and flatter on off, perhaps the flipper. Harry Brook expects it to spin away as he rocks back in an attempt to cut it square of the wicket on the off-side. Is done in by the skidiness on the ball and the ball crashes into the off-stump. SRH are in a lot of trouble now. Harry Brook b Chahal 13(21) [4s-1]

Boult to Tripathi, out Caught by Holder!! What a catch! Tripathi is going nowhere. He thinks it is a bump-ball. Surprisingly Tripathi reviews and umpire KN Anantha Padmanabhan is having a word with the batter. Is this an umpire's review or a batter's review? It is the batter's. Outstanding catch by the tall Holder, stretching his left-hand and grabbing it at a wide slip. Tripathi came down the track and opened the face on this full outswinger outside off, guided it wide of Holder but the big man just plucked it from thin air. One of the moments of the IPL season already. SRH lose their review too. Tripathi c Holder b Boult 0(2)

Boult to Abhishek Sharma, out Bowled!! What an outswinging yorker. Peach. Boult at his best. Abhishek Sharma helped him by staying leg-side of the ball as he tried to dig it out, the ball swings away and knocks back off-stump. Perfect start for RR. Abhishek Sharma b Boult 0(3)

T Natarajan to Samson, out Caught by Abhishek Sharma!! Superb balancing act with the left-foot from Abhishek at deep mid-wicket and he sends Samson back. A back of a length delivery outside off, Samson swiped and nearly got it all the way, Abhishek was there on the edge of the cushions, takes it and then juggles his left-foot beautifully to not touch the skirting. Samson c Abhishek Sharma b T Natarajan 55(32) [4s-3 6s-4]

T Natarajan to Riyan Parag, out Caught by Fazalhaq Farooqi!! The timeout takes a wicket. How often does that happen. A length delivery, the slower off-cutter across Riyan Parag who gets forward to heave and a thick outside-edge goes straight up, Farooqi at short third man goes back and hangs on this time. Riyan Parag c Fazalhaq Farooqi b T Natarajan 7(6) [4s-1]

Umran Malik to Padikkal, out Bowled!! Umran Malik cleans up Padikkal and instead of his trademark punch the air celebration, he stops midway and smiles at Padikkal with a big dimple dotting the pacer's face. Lovely. No feet from Padikkal as it stays low from a good length and skids from there, uproots off-stump after beating the defence. SRH fighting back. Padikkal b Umran Malik 2(5)

Fazalhaq Farooqi to Jaiswal, out Caught by Mayank at deep mid-wicket!! Fazalhaq Farooqi gets his 2nd. Dug in short and Jaiswal totally miscued the pull, toe-ends it and finds deep mid-wicket. End of a good knock but now he has to go. Jaiswal c Mayank b Fazalhaq Farooqi 54(37) [4s-9]

Fazalhaq Farooqi to Buttler, out Bowled!! Such a massive wicket that. SRH strike and get rid of the dangerous Buttler. A hard back of a length delivery on the stumps, nips back in ever so slightly, Buttler stays leg-side to punch, the pace beats him and clips the top of off-stump. The off-bail goes away and that's relief for SRH. Buttler b Fazalhaq Farooqi 54(22) [4s-7 6s-3]
